## üì± Cross-Device Compatibility

### iOS Safari Private Browsing
- **Use cross-device storage utilities** for data persistence
- **Implement memory fallbacks** for storage failures
- **Test in private browsing mode** regularly
- **Show appropriate warnings** to users when needed

### Storage Strategy
```typescript
// Use the cross-device storage utilities
import { setCrossDeviceStorageItem, getCrossDeviceStorageItem } from '@/utils/crossDeviceStorage';

// Always use these instead of direct localStorage
const saveData = async (key: string, data: any) => {
  await setCrossDeviceStorageItem(key, data);
};

const loadData = async (key: string, defaultValue: any) => {
  return await getCrossDeviceStorageItem(key, defaultValue);
};
```

### Storage Data Formats
```typescript
// Cross-device storage wraps data with metadata
interface WrappedData {
  value: any;          // Actual data (may be stringified)
  timestamp: number;
  version: string;
}

// Always check if data is wrapped
const unwrapData = (data: any) => {
  if (data?.value && data?.timestamp && data?.version) {
    return typeof data.value === 'string' ? JSON.parse(data.value) : data.value;
  }
  return data;
};

